@mslaurynhill and her children step into the frame for @denimtears Spring/Summer 2026, grounding the collection in a powerful sense of lineage and legacy. ⁠
⁠
The campaign leans into Denim Tears’ signature storytelling—where garments act as vessels for history, while centering family as both subject and symbol. It was the perfect stage for Denim Tears' latest denim, which features a take on its classic cotton wreath as well as a jacquard wreath set. The entire collection is available now via Denim Tears' online shop and in-store locations.

@benetton is heading out West again and this time they’ve got  some cowboys down on the range. Drawing inspiration from western fashion since the 1970s, and throwing in some decidedly 2026 aesthetics in the mix, the Jean’s West brand collection consists of bootcut, cropped, and carpenter silhouettes for men and women. Made with denim in washes that look worn-in and soft from day one, as well as tees, skirts, and bandanas, it’s designed not only to keep you as comfortable as possible, but ready for the road out west.⁠
